WEBVTT

00:10.000 --> 00:22.000
You're Watching 123Movies.to

02:37.857 --> 02:39.916
You gonna get up today, Hannah?

02:41.861 --> 02:43.658
What's this?

02:43.696 --> 02:44.993
That's orange juice, Hannah.

02:45.031 --> 02:48.159
Don't ya know
I'm allergic to orange juice?

02:48.201 --> 02:49.828
Is that on your chart?

02:49.869 --> 02:53.168
How the hell should I know?
It should be.

02:53.206 --> 02:55.333
You're sure you're allergic
to orange juice?

02:56.542 --> 02:59.272
Well, better safe than sorry
I always say.

02:59.312 --> 03:02.509
Let's getcha
a little milk instead.

03:02.548 --> 03:04.106
We go through this
every other week,

03:04.150 --> 03:05.708
it's always news to her.

03:06.886 --> 03:08.751
Wouldn't you like
to get dressed today

03:08.788 --> 03:10.688
and eat with the others?

03:10.723 --> 03:12.850
I wanna see Rachel.

03:12.892 --> 03:15.190
Hannah, Rachel's very sick.

03:15.228 --> 03:17.196
I know she's sick, goddammit.

03:17.230 --> 03:19.357
Only her family can see her.

03:19.398 --> 03:20.365
I'm family!

03:20.399 --> 03:23.857
Don't get yourself all ruffled.
I'll have to give you something.

03:23.903 --> 03:25.928
You know your blood pressure.

03:28.241 --> 03:30.869
You tell Marge
I wanna see her mother.

03:30.910 --> 03:32.400
All right, I'll tell her.

03:32.445 --> 03:34.345
But I told her
day before yesterday

03:34.380 --> 03:35.870
and she said no;

03:35.915 --> 03:37.678
it would just upset you both.

03:38.417 --> 03:40.885
Rachel's gonna die alone!

03:40.920 --> 03:44.219
Her daughter comes
to see her every day.

03:44.257 --> 03:46.282
But Rachel needs to see me.

03:47.426 --> 03:50.224
She must be an old friend,
isn't she?

03:50.263 --> 03:52.493
Friend doesn't even say it.

03:56.602 --> 04:00.834
Please...
You could dress and powder me...

04:00.873 --> 04:03.171
I'll go sit with those
basket cases down the hall

04:03.209 --> 04:05.234
if you'll just let me see her.

04:05.278 --> 04:08.441
You let the
nurse's aide dress you.

04:08.481 --> 04:11.678
You have a good lunch,
then we'll see.

04:26.632 --> 04:28.930
It'd mean a lot
to both of us.

04:28.968 --> 04:32.597
Well, that's what we want.
That's what we're here for.

04:50.489 --> 04:53.686
<i>Can you imagine?
Doing that for a living?</i>

04:53.726 --> 04:56.354
<i>She'll end up in here herself
when she's 80.</i>

04:57.897 --> 05:01.856
<i>At least this room's got
a view and a window that opens.</i>

05:03.803 --> 05:07.830
<i>The freight train goes by
at two every morning...</i>

05:07.873 --> 05:09.568
<i>I listen for it.</i>

05:10.943 --> 05:13.912
<i>I'd kill myself if all
I could see was parking lot.</i>

05:16.849 --> 05:18.908
<i>I wonder if you can
hear the train?</i>

05:31.697 --> 05:34.165
You guys are getting
real good at this.

05:40.373 --> 05:42.102
Good morning, Hannah!

05:42.141 --> 05:44.666
Oh, you have got
some mail this morning!

05:44.710 --> 05:47.577
Oh, I know I saw something
in here somewhere...

05:47.613 --> 05:51.344
Oh, there it is!
It's a postcard from Alaska.

05:51.384 --> 05:54.148
Oh, look at the size
of that fish.

05:54.186 --> 05:58.179
It's a... it's a...

05:58.224 --> 05:59.020
Halibut.

05:59.058 --> 06:03.017
Oh, it's a halibut.
Look! 356 pounds!

06:03.062 --> 06:05.428
How would you even
catch something like that, huh?

06:05.464 --> 06:06.897
How would you like
to go swimmin'

06:06.932 --> 06:08.991
and see something like that
in the water with you, huh?

06:09.034 --> 06:10.433
No thanks.

06:10.469 --> 06:12.801
So would you like me
to read it to you, hon?

06:12.838 --> 06:15.363
I'll just read it to you
like I usually do, okay.

06:15.808 --> 06:21.678
It says, "Hey, Hannah.
The mud got another one.

06:21.714 --> 06:25.150
Love and regards,
Nettie Bobo."

06:25.184 --> 06:26.708
What on earth does that mean?

06:26.752 --> 06:28.947
Do you have any idea
what that means, huh?

06:30.256 --> 06:32.156
Well, I'm sorry, honey
I have just got to go.

06:32.191 --> 06:34.421
But I'll see you tomorrow.
That's some fish.

06:34.460 --> 06:38.021
My hubby would sell his soul
to hook into a fish like that.

06:38.063 --> 06:41.362
Alaska. How do you know
someone in Alaska?

06:48.274 --> 06:50.469
<i>It's people like that
drive me nuts.</i>

06:50.509 --> 06:54.468
<i>Trap us like rats
and then talk us to death.</i>

06:54.513 --> 06:58.244
<i>I can't just walk away
like I used to.</i>

06:58.284 --> 07:02.311
<i>I didn't like somethin',
off I'd go.</i>

07:02.354 --> 07:04.584
<i>That's how I ended up
in Alaska.</i>

07:04.623 --> 07:08.457
<i>No roads. Everybody flew.</i>

07:08.494 --> 07:12.624
<i>I flew over that tundra
like it was my backyard.</i>

07:13.966 --> 07:18.130
<i>Nettie's still there...
82, canoes to work.</i>

07:18.170 --> 07:20.798
<i>Digs tourists
out of the mud flats.</i>

07:20.840 --> 07:25.038
<i>They sink down in that ooze
and stick like cement.</i>

07:26.812 --> 07:30.908
<i>I loved it there...</i>

07:30.950 --> 07:33.578
<i>but I had to come back.</i>

07:33.619 --> 07:37.749
<i>I always had to come back...
For Rachel.</i>

07:37.790 --> 07:40.725
<i>She'd never leave Michigan.
Had the kids.</i>

07:40.759 --> 07:44.217
<i>Peaches to can
and pies to bake.</i>

07:47.766 --> 07:50.735
<i>She looked like someone
dipped her in flour.</i>

07:54.507 --> 07:56.475
<i>She looked like Mt. McKinley.</i>

07:57.676 --> 08:00.577
I like that -
being compared to a mountain.

08:00.613 --> 08:02.581
It was a compliment.

08:03.516 --> 08:05.177
You were gone
so long that time

08:05.217 --> 08:06.980
I thought you were
never coming back.

08:07.019 --> 08:08.145
You got married.

08:08.187 --> 08:09.950
To escape my father's temper,
not you.

08:11.524 --> 08:13.151
I had to get out.

08:13.192 --> 08:14.989
And girls are
supposed to marry.

08:15.027 --> 08:17.495
Well, at least I married
the dullest man I could find.

08:17.530 --> 08:20.090
Yeah, well, he was
a good provider,

08:20.132 --> 08:22.191
but you'd have been trapped
for the rest of your life.

08:22.234 --> 08:24.361
If Mr. Johnson hadn't
had the misfortune

08:24.403 --> 08:26.371
of dying on that excursion boat.

08:26.405 --> 08:32.503
Everyone ran to the side to wave
goodbye and the boat capsized.

08:32.544 --> 08:34.842
Never marry a weak swimmer.

08:36.815 --> 08:40.751
You waited months to write,
till after the twins were born.

08:42.020 --> 08:43.885
You tried to mourn him,

08:43.923 --> 08:47.586
but it was always me
you wanted to cook for.

08:47.626 --> 08:48.684
Don't be smug.

08:50.062 --> 08:51.427
You always thought we were

08:51.463 --> 08:53.328
the only girls
who did what we did.

08:54.066 --> 08:56.694
Whenever and wherever we could.

09:13.752 --> 09:15.276
Of course after it was over,

09:15.321 --> 09:18.256
you'd ask me to leave
and you'd go back to your Bible.

09:19.625 --> 09:22.059
Never seemed to be on my side.

09:22.861 --> 09:24.260
Neither was your family.

09:24.296 --> 09:26.093
They still aren't.

09:26.265 --> 09:28.961
Your daughter
sits with you for hours

09:29.001 --> 09:30.969
but she won't let me see you.

09:31.537 --> 09:35.303
Has the nerve to tell me
it's for my own good.

09:38.944 --> 09:43.404
I'd like to look at you
just once and die.

09:44.650 --> 09:46.345
Be a nice way to go.

09:48.287 --> 09:50.255
Isn't this a switch.

09:52.124 --> 09:55.093
For once you're staying in one
place and I'm the one leaving.

09:58.130 --> 10:00.928
I had to go.
I had to see things.

10:00.966 --> 10:04.766
Oh, Alaska,
New Mexico, Paris.

10:04.803 --> 10:06.668
My Lord, even Ohio.

10:06.705 --> 10:08.229
Now why Ohio?

10:08.273 --> 10:09.604
It's Michigan, only flat.

10:09.642 --> 10:12.270
Some of Ohio is very pretty.
You've just never seen it.

10:15.314 --> 10:18.181
Every once in a while
you just had to leave me.

10:18.217 --> 10:21.550
You knew I'd be wild for you
when you finally got back.

10:25.491 --> 10:27.459
I've been everywhere...

10:28.661 --> 10:30.424
Even South America.

10:31.997 --> 10:35.125
That's where I found
the seeds for your moonflowers.

10:36.168 --> 10:37.430
Mr. Johnson...

10:37.469 --> 10:39.403
used to walk around with
his eyes down on the ground,

10:39.438 --> 10:41.065
like he was
looking for lost change.

10:41.940 --> 10:44.670
He wouldn't know
a moonflower from a lilac bush.

10:51.817 --> 10:54.547
What do wives find to
talk about with their husbands?

10:55.487 --> 10:57.921
Mr. Johnson and I
ran out of conversation

10:57.956 --> 11:00.117
in less than two years.

11:01.026 --> 11:02.823
You and I never did.

11:03.696 --> 11:07.325
Nope.

11:07.366 --> 11:09.163
Sometimes we'd sit
in the yard

11:09.201 --> 11:11.795
and watch your
moonflowers come out;

11:11.837 --> 11:14.863
they'd unfold in seconds,

11:14.907 --> 11:17.239
just bloomin' in the night.

11:18.711 --> 11:23.273
Then later in the night
I'd call you my moonflower...

11:23.315 --> 11:26.284
when I was pressed up
under your nightgown.

11:31.657 --> 11:34.319
And by morning
the moonflowers had shriveled

11:34.359 --> 11:37.055
and you had
your hairnet back on.

11:37.096 --> 11:38.688
How was I supposed
to cook breakfast

11:38.731 --> 11:40.062
without my hairnet?

11:41.633 --> 11:44.864
You have the most
beautiful hair.

11:44.903 --> 11:46.427
Oh, Hannah.

11:46.472 --> 11:48.269
Don't start something
we can't finish.

11:51.744 --> 11:53.371
Hello, Hannah!

11:54.079 --> 11:57.480
Jesus, Marge, I can hear!

11:57.516 --> 11:59.848
I just can't walk
or see worth a shit.

12:00.586 --> 12:03.350
The nurse says you've been
wanting to see Mom.

12:03.388 --> 12:04.878
Of course I have.

12:04.923 --> 12:07.221
We can't have you
upsetting her.

12:07.259 --> 12:08.351
Upset?! Wh...

12:08.393 --> 12:10.554
When did I ever
upset your mother?

12:10.596 --> 12:12.564
All her life.

12:12.598 --> 12:16.967
Well, if that's the case,
it was her choice.

12:19.772 --> 12:23.538
Marge, please let me see her.

12:23.575 --> 12:24.974
We need to see each other.

12:25.010 --> 12:27.478
This is no way for us
to end our lives -

12:27.513 --> 12:29.242
in two separate rooms.

12:29.281 --> 12:31.078
She has her family.

12:31.116 --> 12:32.242
I'm her family!

12:32.284 --> 12:34.912
Please. Don't.

12:34.953 --> 12:36.580
I used to tuck you in!

12:38.590 --> 12:39.887
I told you stories.

12:39.925 --> 12:42.655
I sat with you
when there were storms.

12:44.062 --> 12:46.530
You never knew your father,
but you knew me.

12:47.800 --> 12:49.597
You knew I'd always
look after you.

12:49.635 --> 12:51.296
When you weren't busy...

12:51.336 --> 12:54.430
Going to Alaska or New Mexico.

12:54.473 --> 12:57.340
I sent you postcards.
I sent you presents.

12:57.376 --> 12:58.775
I sent your mother money.

12:58.811 --> 13:00.608
Don't act like
you were there for Mom.

13:00.646 --> 13:02.477
You weren't. We were!

13:02.514 --> 13:04.311
Roy and I were there!

13:04.817 --> 13:07.786
Dammit, you were children.
You had to be there!

13:08.987 --> 13:13.754
Hannah, I grew up
a long time ago.

13:13.792 --> 13:17.922
I lost my Barbara, my daughter,
in a car accident.

13:17.963 --> 13:19.396
I have grown grandchildren.

13:19.431 --> 13:22.992
I cook, I clean, I can peaches.
I recycle my newspapers.

13:23.035 --> 13:24.935
And once a year we drive
to the Mackinac Bridge

13:24.970 --> 13:26.938
and I have a little piece
of fudge by the water.

13:26.972 --> 13:28.530
And then we drive home.

13:29.107 --> 13:30.472
And I mow the lawn.

13:31.844 --> 13:34.540
But when Mom needs me,
I come.

13:35.881 --> 13:37.940
You always came
when you darn well pleased.

13:39.518 --> 13:41.179
You don't know
anything about it.

13:43.689 --> 13:45.987
I will tell Mom
you asked after her.

13:54.700 --> 13:56.224
She was a cute little girl,

13:56.268 --> 13:57.633
but she's been
a pain in the ass

13:57.669 --> 13:59.864
ever since she joined
the Baptist Church.

14:00.873 --> 14:02.101
Hi.

14:03.041 --> 14:04.668
Are you Grandma Hannah?

14:04.710 --> 14:06.177
What?!

14:06.211 --> 14:07.371
The nurse told me

14:07.412 --> 14:08.845
I should speak with
'Grandma Hannah'

14:08.881 --> 14:10.678
about my project for school.

14:10.716 --> 14:11.978
Grandma Hannah?

14:12.017 --> 14:14.178
Jesus Christ,
don't call me that.

14:14.219 --> 14:19.521
Sorry, she must have... uh...

14:19.558 --> 14:21.025
What?

14:22.027 --> 14:24.894
Women's Suffrage?
The Civil War?

14:24.930 --> 14:26.727
What is it you want
my sage advice about?

14:26.765 --> 14:27.697
I'm busy.

14:27.733 --> 14:29.291
The Depression.

14:30.903 --> 14:32.700
I went to Alaska.

14:32.738 --> 14:34.638
Caught everything I ate
except chocolate.

14:34.673 --> 14:35.833
Are you writing it down?

14:36.808 --> 14:38.901
I voted for Roosevelt
because I liked Eleanor.

14:38.944 --> 14:41.037
The war broke out,
I lied about my age,

14:41.079 --> 14:42.876
I joined the WACS,
and I flew planes.

14:43.548 --> 14:46.244
I invested in computer stocks
in the 50s.

14:46.285 --> 14:48.651
That's how come
a Depression rat like me

14:48.687 --> 14:51.520
can afford this beauteous
single room in Hotel Hell.

14:51.556 --> 14:54.719
That's it. Posterity.

14:54.760 --> 14:56.387
You get asked this a lot.

14:56.428 --> 14:59.295
They send all you in here.
Perk me up.

14:59.331 --> 15:00.821
What in the hell
do you think I am -

15:00.866 --> 15:02.026
the public library?

15:02.067 --> 15:02.999
Go ask your parents

15:03.035 --> 15:05.060
what it was like
getting raised in the 60s.

15:05.103 --> 15:06.730
My parents are dead.

15:06.772 --> 15:08.501
Well, so are mine.

15:11.109 --> 15:15.045
Please, take me home!

15:15.080 --> 15:18.447
Please, take me home!

15:19.318 --> 15:24.278
Mama! Mama! Mama!

15:25.290 --> 15:27.622
What an awful place.

15:27.659 --> 15:29.524
Always have a gun handy
to shoot yourself

15:29.561 --> 15:31.620
in case you fall off
a goddamned roof.

15:32.965 --> 15:34.592
In Alaska if I'd fell off a roof

15:34.633 --> 15:36.726
a bear woulda ate me
and made some use out of me.

15:37.469 --> 15:38.936
Sit down.

15:40.973 --> 15:42.941
You've been to Alaska?

15:42.975 --> 15:44.442
I lived in Alaska.

15:45.677 --> 15:47.167
Look at this...

15:47.212 --> 15:49.442
From a friend of mine
who's still livin' up there.

15:49.481 --> 15:51.278
Lord, now you're
robbing the cradle.

15:51.316 --> 15:53.284
And I thought I'd seen it all.

15:53.318 --> 15:54.285
Nonsense.

15:54.319 --> 15:56.617
Living in Alaska's nonsense?

15:56.655 --> 16:01.957
Nah, I'm just mumbling to myself.
Old people do that.

16:01.994 --> 16:06.795
No, Alaska was great.
I was real happy living there.

16:06.832 --> 16:08.959
How'd you survive?

16:09.001 --> 16:12.493
Had a high school diploma.
Taught school in Barrow.

16:12.537 --> 16:15.131
Skinned things.
You get by.

16:15.173 --> 16:19.803
You just went and did it?
Most people dream and stay home.

16:19.845 --> 16:23.144
There is nothing wrong
with staying home.

16:23.181 --> 16:24.671
I'd really like
to go to Africa,

16:24.716 --> 16:26.980
but I'm afraid
if I need a blood transfusion...

16:27.019 --> 16:28.316
Why? You sick?

16:28.353 --> 16:29.320
No.

16:29.354 --> 16:30.480
So don't get sick.

16:30.522 --> 16:33.082
The blood supply in Africa
is so tainted with AIDS.

16:33.125 --> 16:34.490
What if something did happen?

16:34.526 --> 16:36.551
God forbid
something should happen.

16:37.562 --> 16:40.122
Trust me, kid,
you can 'what if' yourself

16:40.165 --> 16:42.156
into a real boring life.

16:42.200 --> 16:44.327
I really don't care
to listen to this.

16:44.369 --> 16:47.304
You call this something?
I went to your wedding!

16:47.339 --> 16:48.806
What?

16:50.042 --> 16:51.634
She's being ridiculous.

16:51.676 --> 16:53.769
Uh... nothin'. Forget it.

16:53.812 --> 16:55.837
So you married?

16:55.881 --> 16:57.644
Nope.

16:58.383 --> 17:01.910
It's hard to tell.
I wonder...

17:01.953 --> 17:04.183
Girls used to wear
pinky rings and men's socks.

17:05.057 --> 17:06.183
How old are you?

17:06.223 --> 17:07.714
Twenty-one.

17:09.394 --> 17:11.589
Maybe she doesn't know,
but I sure knew by then.

17:13.397 --> 17:15.525
Have you ever been married?

17:15.567 --> 17:17.125
Not to a man.

17:17.536 --> 17:19.026
Oh, yeah?

17:19.070 --> 17:21.039
You gonna put that
in your paper?

17:21.073 --> 17:22.300
Maybe.

17:24.675 --> 17:26.303
Is she dead?

17:27.746 --> 17:29.373
Almost.

17:30.382 --> 17:33.351
They got her in some
other wing in this dump.

17:34.619 --> 17:37.486
They won't let me see her.

17:37.522 --> 17:40.923
She's in a coma,
they still won't let me see her.

17:42.327 --> 17:45.023
Trying to protect us
from each other.

17:47.966 --> 17:50.400
People were always doing that.

17:50.435 --> 17:52.562
Is she who you talk to?

17:54.606 --> 17:57.905
I can't go to her,
so I bring her to me.

17:57.943 --> 18:00.070
And she comes on her own.

18:00.112 --> 18:04.139
I still talk to my parents...
especially when I can't sleep.

18:06.118 --> 18:08.586
You're the only person
I've told.

18:08.620 --> 18:10.000
Well, I'm pretty damn safe.

