18:27.139 --> 18:30.233
And now her damn daughter...

18:31.476 --> 18:33.444
That's her legal family,
you know,

18:33.478 --> 18:36.106
so, anyway, here I sit.

18:36.148 --> 18:38.616
And Rachel's right here
in this nursing home?

18:38.950 --> 18:40.144
Beats the hell out of me

18:40.185 --> 18:42.153
what they think
I'm gonna do to her.

18:42.187 --> 18:44.052
I just...

18:44.089 --> 18:46.148
I wanted to say goodbye.

18:46.191 --> 18:48.785
Her daughter's
with her all the time?

18:48.827 --> 18:50.590
Well, she goes home at night.

18:53.098 --> 18:59.037
God, I'm just so afraid
that she's gonna die alone.

18:59.070 --> 19:01.595
Late at night.

19:01.640 --> 19:05.041
That'd be her way,
slip out real quiet-like.

19:07.746 --> 19:10.647
But if it was up to her,
she'd want me there.

19:10.682 --> 19:12.309
Don't be too sure.

19:13.518 --> 19:16.646
You're so funny.
She's being funny.

19:16.688 --> 19:18.781
A nurse told me
that people can visit

19:18.823 --> 19:20.757
24 hours a day
if they want.

19:21.860 --> 19:22.827
Nobody wants to.

19:22.861 --> 19:26.160
But they can.
I mean, I could.

19:26.198 --> 19:28.758
Could come by
at three in the morning,

19:28.800 --> 19:31.633
swing by your room,
visiting you.

19:31.670 --> 19:34.662
Take you for a stroll
to Rachel's room...

19:34.706 --> 19:36.333
You mean that?

19:37.576 --> 19:39.373
Um...

19:39.411 --> 19:41.379
You'd have to help me
into my chair.

19:41.413 --> 19:43.005
Is your back strong?

19:43.048 --> 19:46.176
Don't worry about it.
I play softball and basketball.

19:46.218 --> 19:48.015
Uh huh.

19:48.053 --> 19:49.850
So it's no problem.

19:49.888 --> 19:51.219
Good.

19:51.256 --> 19:53.247
Because she could
go in a year,

19:53.291 --> 19:55.156
or she could go tonight.

19:55.193 --> 19:57.718
And I don't wanna miss her.

19:58.396 --> 19:59.954
Then let's go tonight.

19:59.998 --> 20:01.363
Three o'clock sound good?

20:01.399 --> 20:02.457
Yeah.

20:02.500 --> 20:04.866
How come you're goin'
outta your way for me, kid?

20:04.903 --> 20:06.564
I don't know.

20:06.605 --> 20:09.369
Maybe so somebody'll
help me out when I'm old.

20:09.407 --> 20:11.466
Yeah, don't count on it.

20:12.744 --> 20:14.405
You seen my horses?

20:15.580 --> 20:18.310
Nope.
Got nothin' in here but goats.

20:18.350 --> 20:20.875
You might want to check
the TV room down the hall.

20:20.919 --> 20:23.217
I'll just do that.

20:23.255 --> 20:25.189
How the hell
they got outta the barn,

20:25.223 --> 20:27.316
that's what I wanna know.

20:27.359 --> 20:28.883
This way?

20:28.927 --> 20:30.895
Turn left
at the drinking fountain.

20:33.265 --> 20:34.892
See ya around, toots.

20:37.269 --> 20:39.237
He a regular?

20:39.271 --> 20:41.102
Never seen him before.

20:42.641 --> 20:44.836
At least he's got
all his parts.

20:44.876 --> 20:47.572
It's those diabetics
with stumps for legs

20:47.612 --> 20:49.944
that depress
the hell out of me.

20:49.981 --> 20:52.245
Especially when
I knew 'em before, you know.

20:52.284 --> 20:54.252
Some of these kids
are from school.

20:56.288 --> 20:57.687
Is there anything you need?

20:57.722 --> 20:59.349
Anything I can
bring you tonight?

21:02.127 --> 21:03.594
Just Rachel.

21:04.796 --> 21:06.923
<i>Three o'clock.</i>

21:06.965 --> 21:08.592
Thanks, kiddo.

21:10.835 --> 21:12.325
That's not the first time

21:12.370 --> 21:14.634
you've waved somebody
under my nose.

21:14.673 --> 21:16.470
That missionary...

21:16.508 --> 21:19.602
followed you
all the way from Brazil.

21:19.644 --> 21:21.407
Do I have to hear
about her again?

21:21.446 --> 21:23.209
I mean it's ancient history.

21:23.248 --> 21:25.079
Clean food and American toilets

21:25.116 --> 21:27.141
is what looked good
to her, not me.

21:27.185 --> 21:29.779
Everything she ate
down there gave her the runs.

21:29.821 --> 21:32.813
Why do you have
to give every little detail?

21:32.857 --> 21:34.620
You always were one
to pull the curtains.

21:34.659 --> 21:36.422
Some things are private.

21:37.162 --> 21:39.824
You mean hidden...

21:39.864 --> 21:41.388
Pretending.

21:42.467 --> 21:45.527
Your dead husband's
photograph on the mantel

21:45.570 --> 21:48.869
and flowers on his grave
on Decoration Day.

21:48.907 --> 21:49.965
And there you were

21:50.008 --> 21:52.636
with all the good widows
at the cemetery.

21:52.677 --> 21:54.804
Then you'd come back home
and hop back in bed with me.

21:54.846 --> 21:56.473
I can't talk to you.

21:56.514 --> 21:57.640
You sure used to.

21:57.682 --> 21:58.649
I'm going back to my room.

21:58.683 --> 21:59.911
Fine.

22:09.527 --> 22:12.496
Used to be we'd make up
by doing the deed.

22:14.666 --> 22:17.464
I'd stay after you until
I had all your clothes off.

22:19.037 --> 22:20.504
<i>Don't you dare follow me.</i>

22:20.538 --> 22:22.597
Baby, I'll only be in Brazil
for a month,

22:22.640 --> 22:24.665
and the money is good.

22:25.777 --> 22:27.608
My God...

22:27.645 --> 22:30.341
A whole month
without your apple pie.

22:30.382 --> 22:32.407
A month without the smell
of your hair.

22:34.586 --> 22:36.349
A month without your eyes...

22:36.388 --> 22:37.412
Shut up.

22:42.894 --> 22:45.021
I'm still mad at you.

22:45.063 --> 22:46.223
I know.

22:48.066 --> 22:50.227
<i>I still feel it.</i>

22:50.268 --> 22:53.203
I want you
just like I always did.

22:53.238 --> 22:55.866
Not the way I am now,
plugged in like a lamp.

22:56.574 --> 22:59.168
Well, it's that
time again, Hannah.

22:59.210 --> 23:01.075
Let's put you on the toilet.

23:02.247 --> 23:03.737
But I haven't eaten anything.

23:03.782 --> 23:05.875
I don't need cleaning out
if I haven't eaten anything.

23:05.917 --> 23:07.714
You know we do it
every three days.

23:07.752 --> 23:08.719
It's on your chart.

23:08.753 --> 23:11.381
But I'm not bound up, dammit.

23:11.423 --> 23:13.721
Well, that's thanks to this.

23:13.758 --> 23:15.885
My body's gonna forget
how to shit on its own

23:15.927 --> 23:17.360
if you keep
shoving that up me.

23:17.395 --> 23:18.225
Just leave me alone.

23:18.263 --> 23:20.731
Hannah, we don't want
to have to restrain you.

23:20.765 --> 23:22.392
Just try it.

23:22.434 --> 23:24.561
Doctor knows
what's best for you.

23:24.602 --> 23:27.002
I haven't seen that
little asshole in three months.

23:27.038 --> 23:28.903
How does he know what I need?

23:28.940 --> 23:31.636
Look, I don't get paid
a fortune for doing this.

23:31.676 --> 23:34.440
I've got enough on my plate
without having to argue with you.

23:34.479 --> 23:35.411
I don't have the time.

23:35.447 --> 23:36.778
There's more to
taking care of people

23:36.815 --> 23:38.806
than reaming them out
every other day.

23:38.850 --> 23:40.477
Don't I have any rights?

24:01.806 --> 24:04.707
<i>There's endless beauty
in Alaska, Rachel,</i>

24:04.742 --> 24:07.040
<i>but some days
it's almost too much.</i>

24:09.547 --> 24:12.846
<i>I want beauty I can hold...
You.</i>

24:16.754 --> 24:19.621
<i>The bald eagles are just like
everything else here -</i>

24:19.657 --> 24:21.921
<i>bigger than you can imagine.</i>

24:21.960 --> 24:24.520
<i>And the mountains
grow like wildflowers.</i>

24:27.499 --> 24:29.763
<i>It'd be heaven on earth
if you were here.</i>

24:31.102 --> 24:34.503
<i>Rachel, what's so wrong
with wanting to see the world?</i>

24:34.539 --> 24:38.498
<i>I can't spend my life
lookin' out just one window.</i>

24:38.543 --> 24:42.309
<i>But mountains, eagles,
Broadway marquees -</i>

24:42.347 --> 24:44.645
<i>what's any of that
when I hold it up to you?</i>

24:46.684 --> 24:48.618
<i>Well, I gotta sign off.</i>

24:48.653 --> 24:52.248
<i>This is gonna cost me an arm
and a leg in postage as it is.</i>

24:52.290 --> 24:56.454
<i>I wish you'd write.
A penny postcard, something?</i>

24:57.595 --> 25:01.429
<i>Don't stay mad.
Please...</i>

25:01.466 --> 25:03.491
<i>I had to leave.</i>

25:03.535 --> 25:06.333
<i>I couldn't stay there
and see you with him.</i>

25:07.872 --> 25:10.841
<i>I love you, Rachel,
I truly do.</i>

25:10.875 --> 25:13.070
<i>And I wish you well.</i>

25:13.111 --> 25:15.545
<i>Think of me sometimes...</i>

25:15.580 --> 25:19.016
<i>Your old friend,
Hannah Free.</i>

25:26.057 --> 25:28.719
Hannah, wake up.
It's time to go see Rachel.

25:28.760 --> 25:30.352
I found her room.

25:30.395 --> 25:31.623
The coast is clear.

25:31.663 --> 25:33.096
Let me just
get your wheelchair.

25:33.131 --> 25:35.429
Uh, do you have to
go to the bathroom?

25:35.466 --> 25:37.525
I'm sorry, yes, I do.

25:37.569 --> 25:39.093
I always have to go
when I wake up.

25:39.137 --> 25:40.866
No big deal.
Do you use a bedpan?

25:40.905 --> 25:41.872
No!

25:41.906 --> 25:44.374
Don't you let her go
in that bathroom with you.

25:44.409 --> 25:45.535
Get a grip on yourself.

25:45.577 --> 25:48.205
Get a grip on me;
Let me help you up.

25:48.246 --> 25:50.714
I can't believe I'm finally
gonna get to see her.

25:50.748 --> 25:53.376
Don't wake me.
I'm sleeping soundly.

25:53.418 --> 25:54.385
We'll be quiet.

25:54.419 --> 25:55.215
What?

25:55.253 --> 25:56.220
Ghost.

25:56.254 --> 25:58.051
Don't call me a ghost.

25:58.089 --> 25:59.556
These aren't my slippers.

25:59.591 --> 26:01.218
Yeah. Bought you a new pair.

26:01.259 --> 26:02.556
What, are you adopting me?

26:02.594 --> 26:03.720
Maybe.

26:03.761 --> 26:05.228
You are hard up.

26:05.263 --> 26:06.230
Lean on me.

26:06.264 --> 26:08.391
Bring the chair.
I can do it, I can get in.

26:08.433 --> 26:10.560
You're always
so darn independent.

26:10.602 --> 26:13.070
Always so damn independent?

26:13.104 --> 26:15.129
Right here.
Lock the wheels.

26:24.282 --> 26:25.647
I appreciate this.

26:53.311 --> 26:55.779
<i>Dammit, Linda!
Dammit, Linda!</i>

27:50.702 --> 27:52.397
I'll just be here,
out of the way.

28:21.899 --> 28:25.699
God, you could run a farm
on all this fuckin' machinery.

28:27.004 --> 28:28.904
All these goddamn tubes.

28:30.675 --> 28:31.972
Poor kid.

28:38.916 --> 28:41.612
You go ahead and sleep, Rachel.

28:41.652 --> 28:43.415
I just wanna be here.

28:48.426 --> 28:50.451
We were together all our lives.

28:56.934 --> 29:00.995
Together and apart...
Right, Rach?

29:03.274 --> 29:05.139
It's just that I've
never seen her

29:05.176 --> 29:08.441
look unattractive
at all in some...

29:08.479 --> 29:10.106
in makeup.

29:10.148 --> 29:12.275
And I said, I said...

29:12.316 --> 29:13.749
Oh, bring your husband...

29:13.785 --> 29:15.150
Gimme, gimme!

29:16.454 --> 29:19.582
Hannah!
You're in the wrong room.

29:19.624 --> 29:21.421
No, I'm not.

29:21.459 --> 29:23.450
Look, Hannah,
you should be asleep.

29:23.494 --> 29:25.553
You're gonna get yourself sick.

29:25.596 --> 29:28.429
How in the world
did you get yourself in here?

29:28.466 --> 29:29.933
I drove.

29:29.967 --> 29:34.927
Hannah, you know how
her family feels.

29:34.972 --> 29:36.940
I'm her family.

29:37.809 --> 29:39.276
Let's take you
back to your room.

29:39.310 --> 29:40.868
No!

29:40.912 --> 29:43.142
What is the harm?

29:43.181 --> 29:45.479
Rachel should not
be here alone,

29:45.516 --> 29:48.610
not now,
not just before dawn.

29:50.254 --> 29:52.745
That's the soul's midnight.

29:52.790 --> 29:56.282
And that's the time
all us old folks die.

29:56.327 --> 29:58.625
Trust me,
people die all day long.

30:02.834 --> 30:04.301
Please let me stay.

30:04.335 --> 30:07.668
I'm sorry, hon, but you're
not supposed to be in here.

30:07.705 --> 30:10.469
Let's wheel you
back to your room.

30:10.508 --> 30:11.304
- No!
- Hannah...

30:11.342 --> 30:11.808
No!

30:11.843 --> 30:15.939
Hannah, you are not
the only person in this home.

30:15.980 --> 30:17.811
I've gotta get
back to the desk.

30:17.849 --> 30:19.976
- You come with me.
- Leave me alone!

30:20.017 --> 30:21.814
This is my great grandma.

30:21.853 --> 30:25.482
I brought Hannah here tonight.
I take full responsibility.

30:25.523 --> 30:27.354
I haven't seen you before.

30:27.391 --> 30:29.359
I flew in a couple days ago.

30:29.393 --> 30:30.621
Now look.

30:30.661 --> 30:33.653
This is
Grandma Rachel's best friend.

30:33.698 --> 30:35.825
Of course she should be here.

30:36.868 --> 30:39.336
It's a funny time of night
to come visiting.

30:39.370 --> 30:41.463
It gives them more privacy.

30:41.505 --> 30:43.973
Why don't you just
go on back to your desk.

30:45.877 --> 30:50.075
Well, maybe for another
15 minutes,

30:50.114 --> 30:52.514
then you take her
back to her room.

30:52.550 --> 30:55.451
I don't wanna find her
in here when I check again

30:55.486 --> 30:57.511
at... 3:45.

30:57.555 --> 31:01.252
I'll take her back at dawn.
She's not hurting anyone.

31:04.395 --> 31:08.354
Oh, all right.
I guess she's not.

31:08.399 --> 31:11.664
But if that daughter of hers
comes before Hannah's gone,

31:11.702 --> 31:13.863
I didn't see
either one of you.

31:13.905 --> 31:15.429
- Deal.
- Okay.

31:19.410 --> 31:21.310
What a load of bull.

31:23.748 --> 31:25.716
I think I'm rubbin' off on ya.

31:25.750 --> 31:27.547
I hope so.

31:27.585 --> 31:31.214
Did ya hear that, Rachel?
I get to stay.

31:52.610 --> 31:54.271
This is Marge.

31:59.784 --> 32:02.252
I want to make sure that...

32:03.287 --> 32:04.584
King me.

32:04.622 --> 32:06.055
Okay...

32:21.973 --> 32:23.941
Hannah, I'll check in
with you later, okay?

32:29.480 --> 32:33.610
That Greta...
she reminds me of somebody.

32:33.651 --> 32:35.278
I'm not lookin' at her.

32:44.996 --> 32:47.226
