38:00.311 --> 38:02.802
Oops! I'm sorry.
More mail.

38:02.846 --> 38:04.507
My, you are popular.

38:04.548 --> 38:05.845
You get more mail

38:05.883 --> 38:08.283
than all the other people
in this place put together.

38:09.486 --> 38:11.113
That's pretty damn sad.

38:11.655 --> 38:13.282
Hmm... Hallmark?

38:14.491 --> 38:16.254
That's for me to know.

38:16.994 --> 38:18.825
Awww...

38:18.862 --> 38:21.023
You look very
tired today, Hannah.

38:21.065 --> 38:22.794
Couldn't you sleep last night?

38:23.567 --> 38:24.966
Now if your eyes are tired,

38:25.002 --> 38:27.129
I'd be very happy
to read that...

38:27.171 --> 38:29.036
I can still read!

38:32.176 --> 38:34.303
Well, would you like
to buy some stamps?

38:34.345 --> 38:35.972
I haven't any money up here.

38:36.013 --> 38:37.071
Yes, you do.

38:37.114 --> 38:39.674
Your little friend left $20
next to the front desk

38:39.717 --> 38:41.947
so you could buy yourself
some little extras.

38:41.985 --> 38:44.044
You want me to get you
a pop from the machine?

38:46.190 --> 38:47.555
Guess not.

38:47.591 --> 38:49.559
Well, the offer stands.

38:49.593 --> 38:51.060
I'll be back tomorrow.

38:51.095 --> 38:53.655
You are always
gettin' somethin'.

38:58.369 --> 39:01.338
I suppose there are some people
who think she means well.

39:03.874 --> 39:05.637
Wars break out
every other week

39:05.676 --> 39:07.940
'cause of some asshole
who means well.

39:27.398 --> 39:28.365
What do you think?

39:28.399 --> 39:29.661
You think anyone in here

39:29.700 --> 39:31.691
knows you're gonna
be my lady tonight?

39:31.735 --> 39:34.704
"My Lady."
Wow... Unbelievable.

39:39.743 --> 39:42.871
<i>So... who's that from?</i>

39:42.913 --> 39:43.937
Friend.

39:43.981 --> 39:45.539
New Mexico?

39:45.582 --> 39:47.880
Yes, and don't get all agitated.

39:49.453 --> 39:50.385
Look at me.

39:50.421 --> 39:53.219
One minute...

39:53.257 --> 39:54.554
thirty seconds...

39:54.591 --> 39:56.718
I'm going back to my room.

39:56.760 --> 39:58.523
No, wait, wait, wait.

39:58.562 --> 40:00.325
I'm paying... attention.

40:01.765 --> 40:03.562
Your mind's in New Mexico.

40:03.600 --> 40:05.192
She's just an old friend.

40:06.103 --> 40:08.071
I'm sure after all those years
working at Los Alamos

40:08.105 --> 40:09.766
she glows in the dark.

40:09.807 --> 40:12.241
Don't tell me how
that woman glows in the dark.

40:12.276 --> 40:15.074
When I'm gone, you'll probably
conjure her up for company.

40:15.112 --> 40:16.579
Her life is full.

40:16.613 --> 40:17.739
You like that about her.

40:17.781 --> 40:19.146
Yes.

40:19.516 --> 40:22.417
Honey, you don't
have to envy her.

40:23.720 --> 40:26.086
She was no match for you.

40:26.123 --> 40:27.750
You always said she was witty.

40:27.791 --> 40:29.349
So are you.

40:30.627 --> 40:33.095
Why doesn't she visit you?

40:33.130 --> 40:38.261
I'm sure that Jackie wants
to remember me the way I was.

40:41.004 --> 40:42.904
I guess I would, too.

40:43.574 --> 40:46.065
I don't want to
see me in her eyes.

40:48.645 --> 40:51.443
So...
Are you coming tonight?

40:51.482 --> 40:52.449
Hope so.

40:52.483 --> 40:53.950
That girl's bringing you?

40:53.984 --> 40:55.918
It's the only way
I can get there.

40:55.953 --> 40:57.784
Why is she helping you?

40:57.821 --> 41:01.621
Because I'm just so
fascinating she can't resist.

41:01.658 --> 41:02.784
Oh, speak of the devil.

41:02.826 --> 41:04.293
- Hi.
- Hey!

41:04.328 --> 41:06.523
I was here earlier,
but you were napping.

41:06.563 --> 41:07.962
I'm surprised you're out of bed.

41:07.998 --> 41:10.967
I'll have you know I've been
up here roaming the halls.

41:11.001 --> 41:13.765
Wow, kid, you really know
how to have a good time.

41:14.671 --> 41:16.298
So how are you?

41:16.340 --> 41:19.138
Tired...
And grateful.

41:19.176 --> 41:20.541
No problem.

41:20.944 --> 41:23.139
I left you a little money
at the front desk.

41:23.180 --> 41:24.374
Now you've
got them tipping you.

41:24.414 --> 41:25.540
I hope you don't mind.

41:25.582 --> 41:27.015
I just know
that you can't keep money

41:27.050 --> 41:28.915
up here in your room
or else it might get stolen,

41:28.952 --> 41:31.318
so this way you can
treat yourself to something.

41:31.355 --> 41:32.822
She is thoughtful.

41:32.856 --> 41:34.653
Well, thanks, kid.
I don't want anything.

41:34.691 --> 41:36.488
Not even a stamp?

41:36.527 --> 41:39.121
Pair of shoelaces?
A magazine?

41:39.162 --> 41:40.561
Read? Tie a shoe?

41:40.597 --> 41:42.622
God it makes me tired
just to think about it.

41:44.167 --> 41:46.965
I had so much energy,
but I squandered it.

41:48.305 --> 41:50.899
Now my body parts
are all worn out.

41:50.941 --> 41:53.000
But I'm still here.

41:53.043 --> 41:56.479
Got my hands,
my heart, my mind...

41:56.513 --> 41:59.004
I'm refining myself
down to the essentials.

41:59.716 --> 42:02.514
So we goin' on vacation
again tonight?

42:02.553 --> 42:04.350
- You willing?
- I am askin'.

42:04.388 --> 42:06.515
- Three o'clock?
- I'll be here.

42:06.557 --> 42:07.819
Thanks.

42:08.559 --> 42:09.856
It's all right.

42:09.893 --> 42:11.884
Hey...

42:11.929 --> 42:13.362
I wanna give you something.

42:14.197 --> 42:15.858
I thought of what
you might like.

42:15.899 --> 42:18.197
Just keep
your clothes on, Hannah.

42:18.235 --> 42:19.668
In there.

42:29.913 --> 42:31.676
It's my journals.

42:31.715 --> 42:33.683
You'll find the Depression
in there someplace.

42:34.751 --> 42:35.877
You mean it?

42:35.919 --> 42:37.147
You'd let me read 'em?

42:37.187 --> 42:38.552
I can quote from 'em?

42:38.589 --> 42:40.216
I thought somebody should
get some good out of 'em.

42:40.257 --> 42:43.226
I'll try to skip over
all the personal stuff.

42:43.260 --> 42:44.488
It's all right.

42:44.528 --> 42:46.655
If you can read
my handwriting, honey,

42:46.697 --> 42:48.562
you're welcome to 'em.

42:48.599 --> 42:50.794
So there you go.
Maybe you'll learn something.

42:50.834 --> 42:51.960
I bet I will.

42:52.002 --> 42:53.560
I bet she will.

42:53.604 --> 42:55.231
See you tonight.

42:55.272 --> 42:56.398
It's a date.

42:59.610 --> 43:01.578
<i>It's a date.</i>

43:02.446 --> 43:04.573
Aren't you just
the nursing home Romeo.

43:04.615 --> 43:06.173
Well, she is pretty cute.

43:07.384 --> 43:11.047
Something 'bout the way
she walks reminds me of you.

43:12.956 --> 43:15.584
You have such a great ass.

43:15.626 --> 43:17.992
Is that why you couldn't
keep your hands off of it?

43:18.028 --> 43:21.259
Near death has really
brought out your racy side.

43:21.298 --> 43:24.756
You old flirt.
You never let me read those.

43:24.801 --> 43:25.597
You're in 'em.

43:25.636 --> 43:27.433
I hope you were kind.

43:27.471 --> 43:29.132
Not always...

43:30.107 --> 43:30.937
They're not just journals.

43:30.974 --> 43:33.272
I wrote a novel
when I was snowed in.

43:33.310 --> 43:35.039
Beat alcoholism.

43:35.646 --> 43:37.341
Am I in that too?

43:38.982 --> 43:41.280
I think you'll
recognize yourself.

43:41.318 --> 43:43.286
Why'd you give them to her?

43:45.489 --> 43:48.287
I want somebody
to know I was here.

43:48.325 --> 43:49.792
Well, I know.

43:49.826 --> 43:52.351
I want somebody to know
you were here too.

43:53.764 --> 43:54.696
The real you -

43:54.731 --> 43:57.427
not the you smiling
at church bake sales.

43:58.568 --> 44:00.695
I wanted people
to know about us...

44:02.139 --> 44:05.040
who's not afraid
of what 'us' means.

44:07.711 --> 44:09.611
I want somebody to know

44:09.646 --> 44:13.343
that I took you to bed...
and I loved you.

44:14.518 --> 44:16.486
We know.

44:16.520 --> 44:18.818
Yeah, but what about posterity?

44:18.855 --> 44:20.152
Posterity?

44:20.190 --> 44:21.157
Yeah.

44:21.191 --> 44:22.852
Good Lord, what next?

44:24.361 --> 44:25.658
Well?

44:25.696 --> 44:26.663
Well what?

44:26.697 --> 44:28.324
What are you doin' in here?

44:29.032 --> 44:30.659
Isn't this my room?

44:30.701 --> 44:31.963
No!

44:32.002 --> 44:34.266
You old men
are in the basement.

44:34.304 --> 44:36.238
Go ask the nurse
to show ya.

44:36.873 --> 44:38.500
I'm lost.

44:39.710 --> 44:41.075
I know you're lost.

44:41.111 --> 44:44.740
Ask the nurse
to take you to your room.

44:45.382 --> 44:47.009
Do I know you?

44:48.051 --> 44:50.849
I wish I had a picture
of you when you were younger.

44:50.887 --> 44:52.445
What's your name?

44:54.725 --> 44:56.693
You wanna take a guess?

44:56.727 --> 44:57.853
No.

44:58.895 --> 45:00.863
Well, then tell me
who you are.

45:03.066 --> 45:04.693
How soon do ya
have to know?

45:04.735 --> 45:06.362
<i>Here you are.</i>

45:08.071 --> 45:10.369
He never knows
where his room is.

45:10.407 --> 45:12.034
Come on, let's get you
back to your room.

45:12.075 --> 45:13.440
I know you.

45:14.411 --> 45:17.209
Not anymore you don't.

45:17.247 --> 45:19.715
Your friend,
she don't talk much.

45:22.419 --> 45:23.943
You should take a nap.

45:25.088 --> 45:26.385
Your little friend will be

45:26.423 --> 45:28.220
waking you up
before you know it.

45:29.259 --> 45:31.022
I used to wake you up.

45:32.429 --> 45:35.728
I'd wake up and my nightgown
would be unbuttoned.

45:42.939 --> 45:45.237
Honey, it's light out.
I've gotta get up.

45:45.275 --> 45:47.300
It's cold outside the covers.

45:48.612 --> 45:51.911
Gotta feed the chickens,
make breakfast for the kids...

45:51.948 --> 45:53.609
I'll feed the chickens.

45:59.790 --> 46:02.088
Take your long johns off.

46:02.125 --> 46:03.683
You first.

46:11.134 --> 46:12.533
It is cold.

46:36.860 --> 46:39.420
I hope that's not in
those books you gave that girl.

46:41.832 --> 46:44.300
I wonder if she has
a little girlfriend.

46:46.236 --> 46:49.535
I'll bet you anything
that she's just like us.

46:52.843 --> 46:56.335
I never could convince you
that we weren't the only ones.

46:59.749 --> 47:01.876
You never thought
what we did was right.

47:03.019 --> 47:04.646
Don't be silly.

47:05.956 --> 47:07.617
Didn't we sit
on my front porch

47:07.657 --> 47:09.716
holding hands,
watching the sunset?

47:11.361 --> 47:14.023
Maybe not when we were 30,
but when we were 60.

47:14.064 --> 47:15.156
Well, then they just thought

47:15.198 --> 47:16.961
we were a couple
of cute old ladies.

47:18.034 --> 47:20.002
No one ever thought
you were cute.

47:21.171 --> 47:23.605
Everyone in this town
knows what you are, Hannah,

47:23.640 --> 47:26.165
so they know about me too.

47:26.209 --> 47:28.643
<i>I sat there
knowing full well</i>

47:28.678 --> 47:30.873
<i>I was hanging out
my bed sheets.</i>

47:30.914 --> 47:32.814
<i>It meant so much to you</i>

47:32.849 --> 47:35.818
<i>that I finally just
let go of my privacy.</i>

47:39.289 --> 47:43.419
<i>And let people,
family, neighbors...</i>

47:43.460 --> 47:46.429
<i>know exactly who I am.</i>

47:47.230 --> 47:48.754
Now...

47:48.798 --> 47:51.460
You show me somebody
in one of your magazines

47:51.501 --> 47:53.469
from California that does that.

47:55.639 --> 47:58.608
I stood my ground,

47:58.642 --> 48:01.076
lived my life,

48:01.111 --> 48:03.443
and I loved you...

48:05.048 --> 48:07.778
despite everything
I was brought up to believe.

48:15.258 --> 48:16.691
I'm tired.

48:20.931 --> 48:22.558
So am I.

48:25.936 --> 48:28.234
I wish we could
take a nap together.

48:28.939 --> 48:30.406
I'll be there.

48:42.452 --> 48:44.249
Quiet around without them.

48:44.287 --> 48:45.549
I'm sure they're having

48:45.588 --> 48:47.522
a great time
camping with the Wilsons,

48:47.557 --> 48:48.421
mosquitos and all.

48:48.458 --> 48:50.926
The Wilsons are
a little churchy for me.

48:50.961 --> 48:52.326
I suppose you want me

48:52.362 --> 48:54.421
to find some heathens
to take my children camping.

48:54.464 --> 48:56.091
Might be more fun.

48:56.132 --> 48:57.099
Ohhh!

49:04.975 --> 49:06.909
It's almost time
for Arthur Godfrey.

49:06.943 --> 49:08.501
You want me
to turn it on for you?

49:09.312 --> 49:11.109
He makes you fall asleep.

49:11.147 --> 49:12.774
I need my rest.

49:14.818 --> 49:16.843
Mmm... that's good.

49:34.838 --> 49:36.465
I already pulled the shades.

51:25.782 --> 51:29.081
<i>You keep after me to write you
more than three sentences.</i>

51:29.119 --> 51:30.916
<i>It took me half an hour
to find a pencil,</i>

51:30.954 --> 51:32.945
<i>but here goes.</i>

51:34.124 --> 51:35.819
<i>The ground is frozen.</i>

51:35.859 --> 51:38.054
<i>We've had snow.</i>

51:38.094 --> 51:39.789
<i>The Canada geese
are on the lake,</i>

51:39.829 --> 51:41.694
<i>taking a rest
on their way south.</i>

51:43.700 --> 51:45.167
<i>I miss you, Hannah.</i>

51:45.201 --> 51:47.669
<i>I wish you'd stay home,
but at least this time</i>

51:47.704 --> 51:49.433
<i>I know you're doing war work.</i>

51:50.073 --> 51:52.405
<i>New Mexico sounds beautiful.</i>

51:53.743 --> 51:54.903
<i>You've been having dinner</i>

51:54.944 --> 51:57.003
<i>with the same woman
all the time.</i>

51:57.046 --> 51:59.014
<i>What's that mean, 'dinner'?</i>

51:59.048 --> 52:02.540
<i>Well, I'm not knitting you
any more warm socks,</i>

52:02.585 --> 52:04.644
<i>if you're down there
'having dinner'</i>

52:04.687 --> 52:07.417
<i>while I'm up here
squirming in my sleep.</i>

52:07.457 --> 52:11.223
<i>I know people read your mail,
so I won't say any more.</i>

52:14.164 --> 52:15.893
<i>I don't know
how many more times</i>

52:15.932 --> 52:17.695
<i>I can let you leave me.</i>

52:17.734 --> 52:19.326
<i>At least I'm busy.</i>

52:19.369 --> 52:20.734
<i>I'm working
three days a week</i>

52:20.770 --> 52:22.670
<i>at the hardware store,
bookkeeping.</i>

52:22.705 --> 52:23.933
<i>The man who used to</i>

52:23.973 --> 52:25.565
<i>keep their books
is serving in Italy.</i>

52:26.743 --> 52:28.904
<i>I'm so thankful
you're not overseas.</i>

52:31.347 --> 52:33.975
<i>Be careful
in New Mexico, Hannah.</i>

52:34.017 --> 52:35.882
<i>Watch out for snakes.</i>

52:35.919 --> 52:37.716
<i>Check your boots.</i>

52:37.754 --> 52:39.221
<i>Come home soon.</i>

52:40.690 --> 52:44.148
<i>You know I love you,
but I'll say it anyway.</i>

52:45.361 --> 52:47.659
"Know ye the Lord,
He is God;

52:47.697 --> 52:49.358
it is He
that hath made us,

52:49.399 --> 52:52.493
and not we ourselves;
we are His people..."

52:52.535 --> 52:53.331
Who the hell are you?

52:53.369 --> 52:55.894
"...and the sheep
of His pasture.

52:55.939 --> 52:57.497
Enter into His gates
with Thanksgiving..."

52:57.540 --> 52:59.030
I said who the hell are you?

52:59.075 --> 53:01.839
"...and into His courts
with praise."

53:02.212 --> 53:05.181
You can't just waltz in here
and start spoutin' over me.

53:05.215 --> 53:07.683
Mary, I'm here to help you.

53:07.717 --> 53:11.517
And my name's not Mary.
Don't call me Mary.

53:11.554 --> 53:15.183
It says Mary H. Freed
on your door, Mary.

53:15.225 --> 53:17.750
Well, I don't give a
rat's ass what the door says.

53:17.794 --> 53:20.786
Profanity is not the language
of our Lord.

53:20.830 --> 53:23.424
Don't you want salvation?

53:23.466 --> 53:24.626
Don't you want to sleep

53:24.667 --> 53:26.862
in the loving arms
of Our Lord Jesus Christ?

53:26.903 --> 53:28.370
No.

53:28.404 --> 53:30.872
Now Mary, you don't mean that.

53:30.907 --> 53:35.571
My name is Hannah...
Hannah Free.

53:35.612 --> 53:40.379
No one has ever called me Mary,
not even my own mother.

53:40.416 --> 53:41.781
So why don't you just

53:41.818 --> 53:44.378
go talk to some other poor joker
who can't talk back.

53:44.420 --> 53:47.048
I can see I haven't caught you
on a very good day.

53:47.090 --> 53:49.058
I don't have good days anymore.

53:49.092 --> 53:52.528
Knowing Jesus
would lighten your burden.

53:52.562 --> 53:53.790
Believe me...

53:53.830 --> 53:57.061
"The Lord is Good;
His mercy is Everlasting."

53:57.100 --> 53:59.728
So you're on the road to Heaven?

53:59.769 --> 54:02.237
I have my mansion reserved.

54:02.272 --> 54:04.570
And I'm going to hell?

54:04.607 --> 54:08.236
If you don't accept Jesus Christ
as your personal savior.

54:12.115 --> 54:15.516
You paint a pretty
mean-spirited picture of Jesus.

54:15.551 --> 54:18.247
Don't you think
that Judgment belongs to God?

54:18.288 --> 54:21.780
Mary, you are an old woman.

54:21.824 --> 54:24.759
God may be
calling your name soon.

54:24.794 --> 54:27.422
The next time the friendly
hand of Salvation

54:27.463 --> 54:30.432
reaches out to you, Mary,
I'd grab it.

54:30.967 --> 54:33.094
My name isn't Mary.

54:33.136 --> 54:35.536
It's the name you
were baptized with.

54:35.571 --> 54:38.233
It's the name
the Lord will call.

54:38.274 --> 54:40.367
What a friend we have in Jesus.

54:40.410 --> 54:42.207
Never forget that, Mary.

54:42.979 --> 54:44.503
Have a nice day.

54:52.322 --> 54:56.190
You can have your mansion!
I'll be just fine in hell!

54:58.094 --> 55:01.188
I hate this about gettin' older.

55:01.230 --> 55:04.996
Think I'm just flappin' my gums
to stir up a breeze.

55:10.340 --> 55:11.466
Rachel?

55:15.678 --> 55:16.906
Rachel?

55:20.516 --> 55:23.314
Well, if you're not gonna come
I'll get a radio...

55:23.353 --> 55:25.514
drown out those
crazy people in the hall.

55:28.691 --> 55:30.488
Course they probably think
I'm crazy too.

55:32.195 --> 55:34.493
Sittin' here alone
talkin' my head off.

55:39.702 --> 55:44.969
Jesus, someone's got
"As The World Turns" on?

55:45.007 --> 55:46.975
What in the hell
are they doin'

55:47.009 --> 55:48.476
spendin' their
last minutes on earth

55:48.511 --> 55:50.138
listening to
"The World Turns"?

55:51.247 --> 55:53.841
I know.
You loved that show.

55:55.184 --> 55:57.550
Lisa and Nancy and Dr. Bob.

56:02.558 --> 56:05.118
Bedpan. Full.

56:11.734 --> 56:12.894
Rachel?

56:16.572 --> 56:18.199
One last game of checkers?

56:23.546 --> 56:25.104
I'll let you win.

56:28.418 --> 56:29.214
My turn?

56:29.252 --> 56:30.719
- Yeah.
- Okay.

56:34.157 --> 56:35.215
King me.

56:35.258 --> 56:36.748
Shit.

56:38.094 --> 56:39.789
I don't think that was fair.

56:42.432 --> 56:44.866
I'm gonna have that kid
bring me a radio.

56:44.901 --> 56:46.664
I can choose my own noise.

56:54.110 --> 56:56.340
You don't hear
anything, do you, Rach?

57:01.951 --> 57:03.441
You're barely here.

57:08.458 --> 57:10.000
You're tryin'
to leave us all behind,

